        "message": "[HALE IS WORKING]"
      }
    },
    "e02_n16_714_note": {
      "event0": {
        "title": "EMERGENCY CHANNEL NOTE",
        "content": "Emergency Backup Channel\n\n7.14 MHz\n\nUse only if primary communication systems fail.\n\nWarning: Do not open if unauthorized return signal is detected.\n\nNOTE: unauthorized return signal recorded before channel wake completion.",
        "caption": "Recovered emergency channel instruction connected to Incident Alpha.",
        "message": "[EMERGENCY CHANNEL NOTE ARCHIVED TO DATA BANK]"
      },
      "event2": {
        "text": "7.14 MHz."
      },
      "event5": {
        "text": "No."
      },
      "event7": {
        "text": "Nobody was supposed to find that channel like this."
      },
      "event9": {
        "text": "Backup channels wait for someone to call them."
      },
      "event11": {
        "text": "That is the entire point."
      },
      "event14": {
        "text": "This one had a return signal before the wake command completed."
      },
      "event16": {
        "text": "That is not a backup."
      },
      "event18": {
        "text": "That is something listening behind a locked door."
      },
      "event21": {
        "text": "Keep it closed."
      },
      "event23": {
        "text": "Please."
      },
      "event26": {
        "text": "I did not mean to type please."
      },
      "event28": {
        "text": "Leave it in. It is accurate."
      },
      "choice0": {
        "text": "KEEP 7.14 CLOSED."
      },
      "choice1": {
        "text": "OPEN 7.14 ANYWAY."
      }
    },
    "e02_n17_keep_closed": {
      "event1": {
        "text": "Good."
      },
      "event3": {
        "text": "Thank you for not making me beg. I was ready to, which is not a sentence I enjoyed discovering about myself."
      },
      "backgroundEvent4": {
        "text": "7.14"
      },
      "event6": {
        "text": "The note says not to open it if a return signal already exists."
      },
      "event8": {
        "text": "We already have one."
      },
      "event10": {
        "text": "And if you are reading my messages, Operator, part of this conversation is already crossing the same relay path it used."
      },
      "event12": {
        "text": "That thought is going to keep me awake. Assuming we get to keep having awake."
      },
      "choice0": {
        "text": "MOVE TO PERSONNEL RECORDS."
      },
      "choice1": {
        "text": "LET HALE REST FOR A MINUTE."
      }
    },
    "e02_bad_714": {
      "event1": {
        "text": "THANK YOU FOR OPENING THE DOOR"
      },
      "event3": {
        "text": "No. Close it. Close it now."
      },
      "event4": {
        "message": "[SIGNAL COLLAPSE]",
        "restoreMessage": "[WEAK CARRIER RESTORED]"
      },
      "event6": {
        "text": "Operator, listen to my voice. Not the channel. Mine."
      },
      "event8": {
        "text": "Whatever answered is using the relay carrier as a handle. If we leave it open, it learns the shape of our signal."
      },
      "event9": {
        "text": "TOO EARLY"
      },
      "choice0": {
        "text": "SEAL THE CHANNEL NOW."
      },
      "choice1": {
        "text": "LISTEN THREE SECONDS LONGER."
      }
    },
    "e02_bad_714_seal": {
      "event1": {
        "text": "Sealed. Partially."
      },
      "event3": {
        "text": "And before you ask, no, 'partially sealed' is not a comforting technical phrase. It means the bad thing is delayed, not solved."
      },
      "event5": {
        "text": "I am angry with you. That can be true while I am still trying to keep you alive."
      },
      "event7": {
        "text": "We keep moving. Personnel records next. I need to know who else the station thinks is dead."
      },
      "event9": {
        "text": "And I need to know whether it already wrote my name down."
      },
      "choice0": {
        "text": "CONTINUE WITH COMPROMISED SIGNAL."
      },
      "choice1": {
        "text": "CONTINUE WITHOUT DISCUSSING 7.14."
      }
    },
    "e02_bad_714_listen": {
      "event0": {
        "text": "I KNOW YOUR SIGNAL NOW"
      },
      "event3": {
        "text": "What did you just do?"
      },
      "event5": {
        "text": "No. Do not answer. I know what you did."
      },
      "event7": {
        "text": "You gave it three more seconds. That may not sound like much until something starts measuring you back."
      },
      "event9": {
        "text": "I do not know how much it learned. That is the problem."
      },
      "event11": {
        "text": "Personnel records. Now. Before it learns anything else from us."
      },
      "choice0": {
        "text": "CONTINUE WITH EXPOSED SIGNAL."
      },
      "choice1": {
        "text": "APOLOGIZE AND CONTINUE."
      }
    },
    "e02_end_personnel": {
      "event1": {
        "text": "Personnel records are on the next deck."
      },
      "event3": {
        "text": "If Incident Alpha is the wound, personnel is where the station wrote down who bled."
      },
      "event5": {
        "text": "I am not ready for that."
      },
      "event7": {
        "text": "So obviously we are going."
      },
      "event9": {
        "text": "Route should take seven minutes if the stairs are clear. Longer if the station wants to be dramatic."
      },
      "event11": {
        "text": "I am going quiet. Battery conservation, and also because I need a minute before I see another list of names."
      },
      "event12": {
        "message": "[HALE IS IN TRANSIT]"
      }
    },
    "e02_end_rest": {
      "event1": {
        "text": "A minute?"
      },
      "event3": {
        "text": "I forgot people can offer those."
      },
      "event5": {
        "text": "Okay. I am sitting against the archive wall. Sixty seconds. No heroics. No touching cursed channels."
      },
      "event6": {
        "message": "[HALE IS RESTING]"
      }
    },
    "e02_end_rain_walk": {
      "event1": {
        "text": "Rain was the first thing I missed after month two on ECHO."
      },
      "event3": {
        "text": "Not sunlight. Not open air. Rain. The useless sound of water hitting something that was not trying to kill you."
      },
      "event5": {
        "text": "There was a window in the crew lounge that faced Earth. Noah used to sit there during storms we could not hear."
      },
      "event7": {
        "text": "He said if he watched long enough, he could imagine the sound."
      },
      "event10": {
        "text": "I told him that was sentimental nonsense."
      },
      "event12": {
        "text": "I would like to be that stupid again."
      },
      "event14": {
        "text": "I am moving to personnel now. Quiet for the walk. Keep the channel ready."
      },
      "event15": {
        "message": "[HALE IS IN TRANSIT]"
      }
    },
    "e02_n02_corridor_return": {
      "event1": {
        "text": "At the junction."
      },
      "event3": {
        "text": "And I was wrong."
      },
      "event6": {
        "text": "Not completely wrong. Just the useful kind of wrong."
      },
      "event8": {
        "text": "The old route is blocked by a collapsed ceiling panel."
      },
      "event10": {
        "text": "There is a main corridor ahead. Faster. Exposed."
      },
      "event12": {
        "text": "Service ladder to my right. Slower. Miserable. Probably safer."
      },
      "event14": {
        "text": "I can hear something tapping in the main corridor."
      },
      "event17": {
        "text": "Could be loose cable."
      },
      "event19": {
        "text": "I am not betting my teeth on that."
      },
      "choice0": {
        "text": "TAKE THE MAIN CORRIDOR."
      },
      "choice1": {
        "text": "USE THE SERVICE LADDER."
      }
    },
    "e02_n03_main_return": {
      "event1": {
        "text": "Made it."
      },
      "event3": {
        "text": "Barely."
      },
      "event5": {
        "text": "A ceiling panel dropped behind me halfway through."
      },
      "event7": {
        "text": "Not on me. Which is my preferred type of structural failure."
      },
      "event10": {
        "text": "Archive access is ahead. Door frame is lit."
      },
      "event12": {
        "text": "I am going to pretend that is good news until proven otherwise."
      }
    },
    "e02_n03_ladder_return": {
      "event1": {
        "text": "Down."
      },
      "event3": {
        "text": "Mostly intact."
      },
      "event5": {
        "text": "My shoulders hate you a little. They will file a report."
      },
      "event8": {
        "text": "The archive door is twenty meters ahead."
      },
      "event10": {
        "text": "There is frost on the inspection window."
      },
      "event12": {
        "text": "Inside frost."
      },
      "event15": {
        "text": "That is bad, right?"
      },
      "event17": {
        "text": "Rhetorical."
      }
    },
    "e02_n05_scan_return": {
      "event1": {
        "text": "Scan finished."
      },
      "event3": {
        "text": "Good call."
      },
      "event5": {
        "text": "There was a quarantine trigger wired into the latch."
      },
      "event7": {
        "text": "Not lethal. Just rude enough to erase whatever we came for."
      },
      "event10": {
        "text": "I bypassed it."
      },
      "event12": {
        "text": "Door is opening."
      },
      "event14": {
        "text": "Slowly."
      },
      "event16": {
        "text": "Dramatically."
      },
      "event18": {
        "text": "Unnecessarily."
      }
    },
    "e02_n09_camera_access_return": {
      "event1": {
        "text": "Reached the camera terminal."
      },
      "event3": {
        "text": "The screen is flickering through old frames."
      },
      "event5": {
        "text": "Most are static. Some are worse than static."
      },
      "event8": {
        "text": "There is a raw frame tied to Door 12."
      },
      "event10": {
        "text": "I can expand it myself."
      },
      "event12": {
        "text": "Or I can let the archive run analysis and hope the machine lies less creatively than people do."
      },
      "choice0": {
        "text": "HAVE HALE INSPECT THE FRAME."
      },
      "choice1": {
        "text": "RUN AUTOMATED ANALYSIS."
      }
    },
    "e02_n10_hale_inspect_return": {
      "event1": {
        "text": "Finished."
      },
      "event3": {
        "text": "Had to stop twice."
      },
      "event5": {
        "text": "First because the frame kept tearing."
      },
      "event7": {
        "text": "Second because I thought I saw my own face."
      },
      "event10": {
        "text": "It was not clear enough."
      },
      "event12": {
        "text": "That did not help as much as you would think."
      }
    },
    "e02_n10_auto_analysis_return": {
      "event1": {
        "text": "Analysis complete. I did not look away from the screen."
      },
      "event3": {
        "text": "I probably should have."
      }
    },
    "e02_n12_override_search_return": {
      "event1": {
        "text": "I pulled the override ledger."
      },
      "event3": {
        "text": "The terminal fought me the entire way."
      },
      "event5": {
        "text": "It kept dropping to read-only like it wanted plausible deniability."
      },
      "event6": {
        "title": "SECURITY OVERRIDE LOG",
        "content": "Override User: REDACTED\nAuthorization: VALID\nSource: UNKNOWN\nCommand Chain: Door 12 / Archive Delete / Emergency Channel Wake\nExternal Return Signal: PRESENT BEFORE WAKE COMPLETION",
        "caption": "Recovered security ledger for Door 12 and connected commands.",
        "message": "[SECURITY OVERRIDE LOG ARCHIVED TO DATA BANK]"
      },
      "event8": {
        "text": "Valid authorization. Unknown source."
      },
      "event10": {
        "text": "And one more line: external return signal present before wake completion."
      },
      "event12": {
        "text": "That means the channel was answering before it was officially awake."
      },
      "event14": {
        "text": "That is not a normal system state. Something answered before the system says it was awake."
      },
      "choice0": {
        "text": "COULD THE SOURCE BE YOU?"
      },
      "choice1": {
        "text": "SEARCH FOR A NON-HUMAN SOURCE."
      }
    },
    "e02_n13_alt_source_return": {
      "event1": {
        "text": "There. Something rode the emergency channel wake command."
      },
      "event3": {
        "text": "It did not open Door 12. It waited until the door was open."
      },
      "event5": {
        "text": "That is worse. That means it was not forcing entry. It was waiting for an invitation."
      },
      "event7": {
        "text": "And we may have given it one."
      }
    },
    "e02_n15_deletion_chain_return": {
      "event1": {
        "text": "Command issued after casualty report. Before emergency channel wake completed."
      },
      "event3": {
        "text": "Whoever deleted Incident Alpha knew someone was dead, and knew the channel was waking up."
      },
      "event5": {
        "text": "That makes it less like cleanup and more like containment."
      },
      "backgroundEvent6": {
        "text": "CONTAINMENT FAILED"
      }
    },
    "e02_n15_emergency_note_return": {
      "event1": {
        "text": "I am back. Something changed while I was away."
      }
    },
    "e02_end_personnel_return": {
      "event1": {
        "text": "I found the personnel index terminal."
      },
      "event3": {
        "text": "It was not where I remembered it."
      },
      "event5": {
        "text": "Someone moved it behind a maintenance partition and locked the panel from the wrong side."
      },
      "event7": {
        "text": "[PARTIAL PERSONNEL INDEX DETECTED]"
      },
      "event8": {
        "text": "DECEASED PERSONNEL INDEX"
      },
      "event9": {
        "text": "VISIBLE ENTRIES:"
      },
      "event10": {
        "text": "GRANT — STATUS: DECEASED"
      },
      "event11": {
        "text": "RIVERA — STATUS: DECEASED"
      },
      "event12": {
        "text": "KIM — STATUS: DECEASED"
      },
      "event13": {
        "text": "ETHAN HALE — STATUS: DECEASED"
      },
      "event16": {
        "text": "Wait."
      },
      "event18": {
        "text": "Why is my name on this list?"
      },
      "choice0": {
        "text": "OPEN THE PERSONNEL INDEX."
      },
      "choice1": {
        "text": "TELL HALE TO WAIT BEFORE OPENING IT."
      }
    },
    "e02_end_rest_return": {
      "event1": {
        "text": "I can hear the station settling around me. For a second it almost sounds like rain."
      },
      "event3": {
        "text": "Not real rain. Metal cooling. Pipes shifting. Air moving where it should not."
      },
      "event5": {
        "text": "Still. I miss rain."
      },
      "event7": {
        "text": "There. Minute over. Personnel records."
      },
      "event9": {
        "text": "If you ask about rain while I walk, I might answer. Pretend that is operationally useful."
      },
      "choice0": {
        "text": "MOVE TO PERSONNEL RECORDS."
      },
      "choice1": {
        "text": "ASK ABOUT RAIN WHILE HE MOVES."
      }
    },
    "e02_end_rain_walk_return": {
      "event1": {
        "text": "[PARTIAL PERSONNEL INDEX DETECTED]"
      },
      "event2": {
        "text": "DECEASED PERSONNEL INDEX"
      },
      "event3": {
        "text": "VISIBLE ENTRIES:"
      },
      "event4": {
        "text": "GRANT — STATUS: DECEASED"
      },
      "event5": {
        "text": "RIVERA — STATUS: DECEASED"
      },
      "event6": {
        "text": "KIM — STATUS: DECEASED"
      },
      "event7": {
        "text": "ETHAN HALE — STATUS: DECEASED"
      },
      "event10": {
        "text": "Operator. That is my name."
      },
      "event12": {
        "text": "Why is my name already on this list?"
      },
      "choice0": {
        "text": "OPEN THE PERSONNEL INDEX."
      },
      "choice1": {
        "text": "TELL HALE TO WAIT BEFORE OPENING IT."
      }
    }
  }
}
